'''The Danish Physical Society''' is the national association for physics for [[Denmark]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dfs.nbi.dk/ |title=Dansk Fysisk Selskab}}</ref> As such, it is also one of the 41 members of the [[European Physical Society]], and contributes to joint European projects such as the [[A Large Ion Collider Experiment|ALICE Collaboration]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aliweb.cern.ch/node/20468 |title=Danish Physical Society &#124; ALICE Collaboration}}</ref> The Society produces a journal titled ''Kvant'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kvant.dk/ |title=Kvant - Tidskrift for Fysik og Astronomi}}</ref> and also seeks to promote the inclusion of more women in physics through its Network for Women in Physics. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://kif.nbi.dk/links.php |title=Netvćrk for Kvinder i fysik}}</ref> This arm of the association also awards the Women in Physics Prize from the Danish Physical Society on an annual basis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dg.dk/en/2012/08/15/women-in-physics-prize-from-the-danish-physical-society/ |title=Women in Physics Prize from the Danish Physical Society « Danmarks Grundforskningsfond}}</ref>

