{{Infobox journal | title = Molecular Plant Pathology | discipline = [[Phytopathology]] | abbreviation = Mol. Plant Pathol. | cover = Molecularplantpathology.gif | editor= Marty Dickman | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[British Society for Plant Pathology]] | country = | history = 2000-present | frequency = 9/year | impact = 3.899 | impact-year = 2011 | website = http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/journal.asp?ref=1464-6722&site=1 | link1 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1364-3703/currentissue | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1364-3703/issues | link2-name = Online archive | OCLC = 44706841 | ISSN = 1464-6722 | eISSN = 1364-3703 | CODEN = MPPAFD | LCCN = 00220243 }} '''''Molecular Plant Pathology''''' is a bimonthly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] published by [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[British Society for Plant Pathology]]. It was established in January 2000 by Prof Gary Foster, University of Bristol, who acted as Editor-in-Chief from 2000 to 2012. The journal covers research concerning [[plant pathology]], in particular its [[molecular]] aspects such as plant-pathogen interactions. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Marty Dickman ([[Texas A&M University]]). According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2011 [[impact factor]] of 3.899, ranking it 20th out of 190 journals in the category "Plant Sciences".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2012 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Plant Sciences |title=2011 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |accessdate=2012-10-28 |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
